 program, saving you extra steps. You can also work with photos from your hard drive. The software automatically checks for duplicate photos and alerts you when it finds one. Once you import your files, you can organize your photos by keyword, date and category or sort them by ratings.","This photo organizer also has a selection of standard photo editing tools; however, the interface of the editor makes it more difficult to use than the other photo organizers we reviewed. Rather than displaying the tools, the software makes you access them using dropdown menus or the batch editor.","With 23 creative filters, you can apply special effects to your photos. You can also perform simple edits like rotate, zoom, crop, resize and remove red eye. The software has color management tools, so you can adjust the color of a photo or convert it to black and white or sepia.","ThumbsPlus does not have the ability to directly share photos to social media sites, but you can send emails or post your photos to online photo galleries directly from the software. You can make a photo slideshow as well. If you want to share hard copies of your photos, the program has printing templates you can use.","The photo organizer’s website offers several support options. You can submit problems to ThumbsPlus using the Problem Report Form, or if you need direct help, the website lists contact information for both phone and email support. The website’s support page provides access to product manuals, FAQs, tutorials and a user forum."]},"id":"2d6ef151-90e3-44e7-8fdd-65927152a656","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"3020cb57-3c2b-49fe-bc4a-e14702743366","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["While ThumbsPlus is not the easiest software to use, it has effective organizing and editing tools you can use to perfect your photos, and it also has a variety of resources to help you learn how to use the software. Its sharing options are limited in comparison to other programs, but this software he